      "id": "detailed_1_listing_0",
      "firm_id": "detailed_1",
      "description": "This vehicle is in fair condition and has been a reliable daily driver for several years. The exterior shows some signs of its age, including minor scratches on the door panels and a small dent on the rear bumper, though there is no major rust. Inside, the upholstery is intact but shows some staining on the passenger seat and typical wear on the driver's side bolsters. Mechanically, the car runs well, though the air conditioning takes a moment to get cold and there is a slight squeak from the fan belt on cold starts. It has been regularly maintained with oil changes every 5,000 miles, and the tires still have about 40% tread life remaining. This is a great, honest car for someone looking for dependable transportation without the price tag of a newer model.",
